HEADWORD: mess up
<hw>mess up</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make
a mess{5} of; to confuse, disorder, or muddle; to muss; to jumble; to
disturb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To botch{3}; to bungle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

